## Golden Rules (non-negotiable — override "best practice")

1. **Never ration tokens for real students.** No per-student quotas, daily limits, message caps, or paywall logic. Rate limiting is bot-only, with generous env-tunable thresholds.
2. **Anonymous users keep full access.** Reading public content and using the AI never requires login. Logged-out users simply get no persistence. **Never add `protect` to AI or public-content read paths.**

Tutor design: Thai-first; critical thinking > correctness; admire the idea first, never say "wrong"; teacher-authored questions/answers/guidelines drive the agent.

