## Git — read before any git command

- **Three repos:** `Hot-Potato/` = workspace meta repo (docs, graphify, archive). `client/` and `server/` = separate product repos (gitignored here).
- Run `git` **in the repo you're changing:** docs/graph → `Hot-Potato/`; app code → `client/` or `server/`.
- Never run git from `C:/Users/BTCOM` (home) — stray `git init` there surfaces unrelated files. If you see foreign files in `git status`, stop — wrong folder.
- Only commit when the user explicitly asks.

