## Common commands

Always `cd` into the half you're working on first.

```bash
# Server — http://localhost:5000
cd server && npm install && npm run dev
cd server && npm test                  # vitest, in-memory Mongo, mocked Gemini
cd server && npm run test:ai           # live Gemini (RUN_AI_TESTS=true + key)

# Client — http://localhost:5173
cd client && npm install && npm run dev
cd client && npm test
cd client && npm run lint
```

**Definition of done:** phase tests written and passing; `npm test` green in every half touched; relevant `CLAUDE.md` updated. Manual smoke: both halves running, test lesson at `/view/69e39d0b60d467bd515a4945`, logged-in **and** incognito.

