## Agent tooling — Playwright MCP

`.cursor/mcp.json` registers the **playwright** MCP server (`npx @playwright/mcp@latest`) — real browser automation (`browser_*` tools: navigate, snapshot, click, screenshot) for driving the `client/` app. **Restart Cursor** after first setup so the tools load. To test the client: `cd client && npm run dev` (Vite :5173), then ask the agent to navigate there and `browser_snapshot` the page.

Claude Code has the same server user-scoped, plus the `frontend-design` design plugin — see @AGENT.md §7.

